edu.sc.seis.TauP

Class SacTimeSeries

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.sc.seis.TauP.SacTimeSeries
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable

    public class SacTimeSeries
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable
    Class that represents a sac file. All headers are have the same names as within the Sac program. Can read the whole file or just the header as well as write a file. Major modification by D.C. Ketchum USGS Feb 2008. Change from using DataInputStreadm and DataOutputStreams to using ByteBuffers to build up the bytes in a file or interpreting them when reading them in. Fixes misc problem with old method of dealing with double encoding when swapping bytes around. Changed all internal fields to double but keep reading and writing of files as floats.

      • writeHeader

        public void writeHeader(java.nio.ByteBuffer dos)
        This routine writes data into the given byte buffer for the header portion. The position in the bytebuffer is moved from its current position forward by the length of the header.
        Parameters:
        dos - The Byte buffer to put the data in.

      • trimNodataEnd

        public int trimNodataEnd(int fill)
        this trims any filled data at the end of a buffer. This option is used in the CWBQuery tool -sactrim option. It resets SAC parameter npts as well are returning the number of points trimmed to the user
        Parameters:
        fill - the fill value to trim from the end
        Returns:
        the number of samples at the end which are filled.
